    <div id="center" >
    
      <h3>Welcome!</h3>
      <p>Welcome to the new homesite of St. Michael's Museum, Genealogy Centre &amp; Catholic Bookstore! <b>St. Michael's Museum Association</b> was founded in 1974 by a group of eight people. With additional members, a growing collection, and  accumulating genealogical records, the Association acquired St. Joseph's Villa in 1979. Association members, supported by government grants and private donations, restored the historic building and reopened its doors in 1980, this time as the house of the Museum's collection. At the same time, <b>St. Michael's Genealogical Centre</b> began its public operations. 

</p><p>In 2004, <b>St. Michael's Catholic Supplies and Book Store</b> was established in the same building. Since then, the Museum, Genealogical Centre and Bookstore have been run by many of the same volunteers.</p>        
    </div>

